# Week 5 Stories – Tree Algorithms Assignment

**Author:** Abhay  
**Date:** 13/02/2026

## Overview

Advanced Binary Tree algorithms, recursion, greedy strategies, and problem-solving techniques.

---

## Problems Implemented

| # | Problem | Key Concepts | Time |
|---|---------|--------------|------|
| 1 | Palindromic Path Finder | Frequency counting, Bitmasking, Palindrome property | O(N) |
| 2 | Vertical Silhouette | BFS, TreeMap, Level tracking | O(N log N) |
| 3 | Distant Cousins | Level order traversal, Parent tracking, Depth comparison | O(N) |
| 4 | Minimum Camera Coverage | Postorder DFS, Greedy states | O(N) |
| 5 | Serializer/Deserializer | Preorder traversal, Queue reconstruction | O(N) |
| 6 | K-Sum Path | Prefix sum, DFS, HashMap | O(N) |
| 7 | Boundary Traversal | Left/right/leaf separation | O(N) |
| 8 | LCA of Set | Recursive LCA, Set containment | O(N) |

